WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:03.680
Do you think that I could get some?

00:00:03.780 --> 00:00:04.339
Shaky, shaky.

00:00:04.639 --> 00:00:06.299
Maybe it's a little thing, guys.

00:00:06.379 --> 00:00:06.900
Sticky, sticky.

00:00:07.179 --> 00:00:09.339
You're my electrical elephant flavor.

00:00:09.800 --> 00:00:12.040
I got to do you till the next song saves you.

00:00:12.380 --> 00:00:14.000
Can I get a little zip, zip?

00:00:14.160 --> 00:00:14.700
Lucky, lucky.

00:00:14.960 --> 00:00:16.640
Can I get a little uh, uh?

00:00:16.760 --> 00:00:17.300
Lucky, lucky.

00:00:17.559 --> 00:00:18.320
And what you say?

00:00:18.460 --> 00:00:19.740
It doesn't matter anyway.

00:00:19.960 --> 00:00:22.219
You won't do another because you're getting with me.

00:00:22.640 --> 00:00:25.080
She got the power of the hoochie.

00:00:25.300 --> 00:00:27.679
I got the fever for the flavor of the coochie.

00:00:28.500 --> 00:00:28.940
Sasha.

00:00:28.940 --> 00:00:30.679
Say something presidential.

00:00:32.420 --> 00:00:33.260
Slow, Chloe.

00:00:33.480 --> 00:00:34.100
Slow down.

00:00:34.439 --> 00:00:36.000
The election hasn't even started yet.

00:00:38.780 --> 00:00:40.359
What do you think Sasha's chances are?

00:00:41.160 --> 00:00:43.359
Well, she knows the most about student government.

00:00:43.640 --> 00:00:44.780
She's worked her way up.

00:00:45.040 --> 00:00:46.079
She's on a ton of committees,

00:00:46.260 --> 00:00:48.460
but she's more of a worker than a leader.

00:00:50.439 --> 00:00:51.240
How about Paul?

00:00:52.159 --> 00:00:54.140
Well, he's certainly the most qualified,

00:00:54.439 --> 00:00:55.579
but elections aren't about merit.

00:00:55.700 --> 00:00:56.540
They're about popularity.

00:00:58.320 --> 00:00:58.920
Which brings me to the question.

00:00:59.079 --> 00:01:00.100
What's Sasha's name?

00:01:00.280 --> 00:01:00.760
My name is Sasha,

00:01:00.920 --> 00:01:01.920
and it's a French word for police.

00:01:02.079 --> 00:01:04.439
Head cheerleader and president of the drama club.

00:01:04.620 --> 00:01:06.200
That definitely gives her an edge,

00:01:06.359 --> 00:01:08.219
not to mention that she's also really hot.

00:01:08.420 --> 00:01:11.599
Yeah, but her name rhymes with the French word for luggage.

00:01:12.000 --> 00:01:12.840
Okay.

00:01:13.019 --> 00:01:15.659
Glad to see you're not reaching for reasons to hate her.

00:01:19.840 --> 00:01:22.620
I saw you taking Sasha's picture.

00:01:22.780 --> 00:01:23.799
Why didn't you take in mine?

00:01:23.960 --> 00:01:25.560
That qualifies as bias.

00:01:25.700 --> 00:01:27.120
For the record, I plan on running photos and bios

00:01:27.280 --> 00:01:28.320
of all the candidates,

00:01:28.319 --> 00:01:30.319
Thank you, Elise.

00:01:30.319 --> 00:01:33.319
Hey, Chloe? What about the editorial?

00:01:33.319 --> 00:01:36.319
You can only endorse one candidate, so who's it gonna be?

00:01:36.319 --> 00:01:40.319
Who cares? No matter what she says, people are gonna vote for me.

00:01:40.319 --> 00:01:44.319
Never underestimate the need for the clinically ambitious to pad their resumes.

00:01:46.319 --> 00:01:50.319
You wanna avoid the pain and humiliation of losing?

00:01:50.319 --> 00:01:52.319
Drop it.

00:01:58.319 --> 00:02:04.319
I know it's not my fault.

00:02:18.319 --> 00:02:20.319
Hi.

00:02:27.319 --> 00:02:28.180
You,

00:02:28.180 --> 00:02:28.259
you Мeng Ати travelling to femme America in JonG� activity,

00:02:28.259 --> 00:02:47.519
Ow!

00:02:58.259 --> 00:03:28.239
Oh, my God.

00:03:28.259 --> 00:03:58.239
Oh, my God.

00:03:58.259 --> 00:04:28.240
Oh, my God.

00:04:28.259 --> 00:04:30.259
Oh, my God.

00:04:30.259 --> 00:04:32.259
Oh, my God.

00:04:32.259 --> 00:04:34.259
Oh, my God.

00:04:58.259 --> 00:05:03.439
Oh, my God.

00:05:03.439 --> 00:05:15.480
Oh, my God.

00:05:20.319 --> 00:05:22.319
What have you done?

00:05:22.319 --> 00:05:24.980
I see a big future ahead of you in politics, Clark.

00:05:24.980 --> 00:05:26.599
You're straightforward. People like you.

00:05:26.599 --> 00:05:27.599
Uh-uh.

00:05:27.599 --> 00:05:28.240
No way.

00:05:28.259 --> 00:05:30.259
Clark, you've got the whole package.

00:05:30.259 --> 00:05:33.259
Looks, brains, and that whole farm boy charm.

00:05:33.259 --> 00:05:35.259
Did I mention the perks of power?

00:05:35.259 --> 00:05:37.259
You know, if it was such a great gig, why didn't you run?

00:05:37.259 --> 00:05:39.259
I know my strengths.

00:05:39.259 --> 00:05:41.259
I'm more the power behind the throne.

00:05:41.259 --> 00:05:43.259
The guy behind the guy.

00:05:43.259 --> 00:05:45.259
The one who makes it all happen.

00:05:45.259 --> 00:05:46.259
Pete Ross, the kingmaker.

00:05:46.259 --> 00:05:48.259
Exactly. All you gotta do is show up,

00:05:48.259 --> 00:05:50.259
shake a couple of hands, give an election speech.

00:05:50.259 --> 00:05:51.259
It's easy.

00:05:51.259 --> 00:05:54.259
We wonder why our politicians aren't great leaders.

00:05:54.259 --> 00:05:56.259
Clark! Clark! Clark! Clark!

00:05:56.259 --> 00:06:03.259
Clark! Clark! Clark! Clark! Clark! Clark! Clark! Clark! Clark!

00:06:04.259 --> 00:06:10.259
Are you napping music?

00:06:11.259 --> 00:06:13.259
Layers.

00:06:14.259 --> 00:06:15.259
Take it out!

00:06:16.259 --> 00:06:17.259
Other.

00:06:18.259 --> 00:06:19.259
Take it out.

00:06:20.259 --> 00:06:21.259
Layers.

00:06:22.259 --> 00:06:23.259
Use the 20.

00:06:24.259 --> 00:06:26.259
uf the letters,

00:06:26.259 --> 00:06:33.420
You look like you could use some help.

00:06:33.740 --> 00:06:34.620
No, I'm fine.

00:06:34.980 --> 00:06:38.199
Hans, I need you out on Route 90, two miles east of the mansion.

00:06:39.019 --> 00:06:40.639
A red Mustang with engine trouble.

00:06:40.839 --> 00:06:41.360
What are you doing?

00:06:42.099 --> 00:06:43.159
Calling my mechanic.

00:06:43.899 --> 00:06:46.759
Not that I don't appreciate your attempt at postmodern chivalry,

00:06:46.839 --> 00:06:47.740
but I said I was fine.

00:06:48.800 --> 00:06:50.740
Dolce and Gabbana and a vocabulary?

00:06:51.719 --> 00:06:53.560
You've got Metropolis written all over you.

00:06:54.000 --> 00:06:55.120
It brings you to Smallville.

00:06:55.120 --> 00:06:57.480
You're the sheriff, come to run me out of town?

00:06:57.819 --> 00:07:00.340
Did the attitude come with the couture, or was it an accessory?

00:07:01.620 --> 00:07:04.019
If you must know, I'm thinking about moving here.

00:07:04.420 --> 00:07:06.680
I'd ask you what it's like, but you don't look like a local.

00:07:08.079 --> 00:07:09.579
I've lived here since last fall.

00:07:10.399 --> 00:07:12.680
First, I couldn't wait to get out, but now it's starting to grow on me.

00:07:12.879 --> 00:07:16.040
Well, why the change? The Norman Rockwell ambience seduce you?

00:07:16.879 --> 00:07:18.000
Appearance is deceptive.

00:07:18.620 --> 00:07:19.899
Nothing around here is what it seems.

00:07:20.220 --> 00:07:21.780
I'm intrigued. What do you mean?

00:07:21.780 --> 00:07:24.560
All these questions.

00:07:25.120 --> 00:07:27.120
This is beginning to sound like an interview.

00:07:33.720 --> 00:07:35.120
Who do you work for?

00:07:35.120 --> 00:07:36.620
I don't know what you're talking about.

00:07:36.620 --> 00:07:39.360
If I toss these into the woods, you really are gonna need a tow truck.

00:07:42.980 --> 00:07:45.780
Carrie Castle. I'm a staff reporter from the Metropolis Journal.

00:07:47.500 --> 00:07:49.220
I don't grant interviews, Miss Castle.

00:07:49.220 --> 00:07:53.319
I spent the better part of my life taking back entrances to avoid people like you.

00:07:53.319 --> 00:07:54.620
Wait, just listen.

00:07:54.620 --> 00:07:56.620
I want to write an article about you.

00:07:58.620 --> 00:07:59.620
That's your pitch?

00:08:00.120 --> 00:08:01.620
Your article's written about me all the time.

00:08:01.620 --> 00:08:05.620
But you're either dismissed as a wild child playboy or the spoiled son of Lionel Luther.

00:08:05.620 --> 00:08:08.120
You've gotten some good press in the Inquisitor.

00:08:08.120 --> 00:08:11.620
But the journal is not a tabloid. It's well respected. It could really help change your image.

00:08:13.620 --> 00:08:14.620
What did you have in mind?

00:08:14.620 --> 00:08:16.620
A cover profile on you and your work in Smallville.

00:08:16.620 --> 00:08:21.620
I promise it will be fair and accurate, and will give you the legitimacy you need to get out from behind your father's shadow.

00:08:21.620 --> 00:08:23.620
Launching my career and conveniently your own.

00:08:24.620 --> 00:08:27.620
I admire the effort, Miss Castle, but I have to decline.

00:08:31.620 --> 00:08:33.620
You get points for style, though.

00:08:46.620 --> 00:08:48.620
I can't believe Pete did this.

00:08:48.620 --> 00:08:52.620
I know. Some men are born to greatness, others are dragged into it, kicking and screaming.

00:08:52.620 --> 00:08:53.620
Mark!

00:08:53.620 --> 00:08:55.620
What's going on? Why are you running?

00:08:55.620 --> 00:08:57.620
You've never shown any interest in student government.

00:08:57.620 --> 00:09:00.620
Don't worry, it's just a gag. Pete nominated me.

00:09:00.620 --> 00:09:02.620
So you're going to take your name off the ballot?

00:09:02.620 --> 00:09:03.620
Yeah.

00:09:03.620 --> 00:09:06.620
Well, good. Because this election is way too important to turn into a joke.

00:09:06.620 --> 00:09:08.620
It's bad enough with Felice.

00:09:08.620 --> 00:09:12.620
I hear she's throwing a pre-election bash with a ban and catering.

00:09:13.620 --> 00:09:16.620
She was trying to buy this election like one of her Prada bags.

00:09:19.620 --> 00:09:21.620
Talk about tightly wound.

00:09:21.620 --> 00:09:22.620
Chloe.

00:09:22.620 --> 00:09:25.620
Not that I'm planning to, but if I ran, do you think I'd have a shot?

00:09:25.620 --> 00:09:27.620
Yeah. Right after I'm elected head cheerleader.

00:09:34.620 --> 00:09:36.620
Clark Kent for president?

00:09:36.620 --> 00:09:38.620
Don't worry, I'm pulling my name out tomorrow.

00:09:38.620 --> 00:09:41.620
Oh. I think this is a terrific idea.

00:09:41.620 --> 00:09:42.620
You do?

00:09:42.620 --> 00:09:46.620
Yeah. You're always saying that you don't get a chance to shine because football's off limits.

00:09:46.620 --> 00:09:48.620
Maybe this is your opportunity.

00:09:48.620 --> 00:09:50.620
I just assumed you'd say no. Student government is such a public thing.

00:09:50.620 --> 00:09:51.620
But it doesn't require you to vote.

00:09:51.620 --> 00:09:53.620
But it doesn't require you to use your gifts.

00:09:53.620 --> 00:09:55.620
And it's a school activity you can make your own.

00:09:57.620 --> 00:09:59.620
What's the matter, son? You don't look too happy about this.

00:10:00.620 --> 00:10:01.620
Hey.

00:10:03.620 --> 00:10:06.620
It's just I've never put myself out there. I've always tried to stay out of the spotlight.

00:10:06.620 --> 00:10:08.620
Well, nobody's saying you have to run.

00:10:08.620 --> 00:10:09.620
Clark, you can quit if you want.

00:10:09.620 --> 00:10:12.620
But remember, quitting's a very hard habit to break.

00:10:14.620 --> 00:10:15.620
No pressure.

00:10:21.620 --> 00:10:23.620
I'll be back.

00:10:26.620 --> 00:10:28.620
Wow. The place is, um...

00:10:28.620 --> 00:10:29.620
Empty.

00:10:29.620 --> 00:10:30.620
Deserted.

00:10:31.620 --> 00:10:32.620
Vacant.

00:10:33.620 --> 00:10:37.620
Well, I was searching for a euphemism to say that, but yeah.

00:10:37.620 --> 00:10:40.620
The Beanery's been trying to put us out of business ever since we opened.

00:10:40.620 --> 00:10:43.620
I have tried coupons, price cuts, even ads in the ledger.

00:10:43.620 --> 00:10:44.620
So far, nothing's worked.

00:10:44.620 --> 00:10:47.620
At this rate, we're gonna have to close the doors in a month.

00:10:47.620 --> 00:10:49.620
Have you spoken to Lex?

00:10:49.620 --> 00:10:51.620
He's an investor. I'm sure he can help.

00:10:51.620 --> 00:10:53.620
He's been uncharacteristically silent.

00:10:53.620 --> 00:10:57.620
Besides, this is my battle to win or lose, and I am determined to win.

00:10:58.620 --> 00:11:02.620
Speaking of which, I hear you've got a battle of your own on your hands.

00:11:02.620 --> 00:11:05.620
Oh, yeah, the election. I'm not really running.

00:11:06.620 --> 00:11:09.620
That's too bad. I think you'd make a great class president.

00:11:09.620 --> 00:11:10.620
Really?

00:11:10.620 --> 00:11:15.620
Yeah. You're honest, people trust you, and you have this innate sense of justice.

00:11:15.620 --> 00:11:19.620
I can see it on your face how upset you get every time you think somebody's being mistreated.

00:11:20.620 --> 00:11:21.620
You see all that in me?

00:11:21.620 --> 00:11:23.620
Yes, I do.

00:11:30.620 --> 00:11:32.620
Clark Kent for president.

00:11:32.620 --> 00:11:34.620
How'd you know I was running?

00:11:35.620 --> 00:11:37.620
I found this on my windshield in town.

00:11:37.620 --> 00:11:40.620
I have an overzealous campaign manager.

00:11:40.620 --> 00:11:42.620
I didn't realize you had political aspirations.

00:11:42.620 --> 00:11:44.620
I don't. I just figured I could make a difference.

00:11:44.620 --> 00:11:48.620
Did you swing by for a campaign contribution?

00:11:48.620 --> 00:11:49.620
Actually, no.

00:11:49.620 --> 00:11:50.620
I'm not sure.

00:11:50.620 --> 00:11:53.620
Actually, I was wondering if you knew about the Talon.

00:11:53.620 --> 00:11:56.620
You mean the fact that it's been practically empty the last two weeks?

00:11:56.620 --> 00:11:59.620
Do you plan on helping Lana out? She's been trying everything.

00:11:59.620 --> 00:12:01.620
She's doing an admirable job.

00:12:03.620 --> 00:12:04.620
If the Talon goes under...

00:12:04.620 --> 00:12:08.620
Clark, I'm not going to subsidize the money-losing operation.

00:12:08.620 --> 00:12:09.620
The Talon has to find its own feet.

00:12:09.620 --> 00:12:12.620
We could at least stop by and show some solidarity.

00:12:13.620 --> 00:12:17.620
See? You're already working for your constituents.

00:12:17.620 --> 00:12:19.620
You want some advice?

00:12:19.620 --> 00:12:22.620
I think you need a better slogan.

00:12:24.620 --> 00:12:26.620
Everybody's used this one, including me.

00:12:27.620 --> 00:12:29.620
You ran for student office.

00:12:29.620 --> 00:12:30.620
Once.

00:12:30.620 --> 00:12:32.620
But my aspirations weren't very noble.

00:12:32.620 --> 00:12:33.620
Did you win?

00:12:33.620 --> 00:12:35.620
Of course.

00:12:36.620 --> 00:12:38.620
Do you have any tips?

00:12:38.620 --> 00:12:41.620
You don't need my methods. You'll win on your own terms.

00:12:42.620 --> 00:12:44.620
The competition's pretty stiff.

00:12:44.620 --> 00:12:46.620
There's nothing wrong with a good fight. Just remember...

00:12:46.620 --> 00:12:48.620
The man of tomorrow is forged by his battles today.

00:12:49.620 --> 00:12:51.620
Could I use that?

00:12:51.620 --> 00:12:53.620
I mean, the man of tomorrow for my slogan?

00:12:53.620 --> 00:12:55.620
Knock yourself out.

00:12:57.620 --> 00:13:00.620
Hey, don't write yourself off yet

00:13:00.620 --> 00:13:02.620
It's only when you're had you feel the power

00:13:02.620 --> 00:13:04.620
You'll put the foot down

00:13:04.620 --> 00:13:06.620
Thank you, Tom. No problem.

00:13:06.620 --> 00:13:08.620
Try your best

00:13:08.620 --> 00:13:09.620
I love you.

00:13:09.620 --> 00:13:11.620
Clark Kent, the man of tomorrow.

00:13:11.620 --> 00:13:13.620
Kind of presumptuous, don't you think?

00:13:13.620 --> 00:13:14.620
I like it.

00:13:14.620 --> 00:13:16.620
I thought you were bagging this whole election.

00:13:16.620 --> 00:13:17.620
I'm not.

00:13:17.620 --> 00:13:18.620
I'm not.

00:13:18.620 --> 00:13:20.620
I had a change of heart.

00:13:20.620 --> 00:13:23.620
The man of tomorrow. Very catchy.

00:13:23.620 --> 00:13:25.620
Thank you. And thank you for the encouragement.

00:13:25.620 --> 00:13:27.620
You've got my vote.

00:13:27.620 --> 00:13:29.620
I was thinking maybe I could have my election rally at the town.

00:13:29.620 --> 00:13:30.620
Help bring people by.

00:13:30.620 --> 00:13:32.620
That sounds great. You know where to find me.

00:13:33.620 --> 00:13:34.620
Bye, Lana.

00:13:34.620 --> 00:13:35.620
Bye.

00:13:35.620 --> 00:13:37.620
You're running because of Lana.

00:13:37.620 --> 00:13:38.620
Why am I not surprised?

00:13:38.620 --> 00:13:40.620
No, I'm running because I think I can do a good job.

00:13:40.620 --> 00:13:42.620
All right, Clark. Whatever.

00:13:42.620 --> 00:13:44.620
Hey, you know, Pete has faith in me and so does Lana.

00:13:44.620 --> 00:13:46.620
It's interesting that you don't.

00:13:46.620 --> 00:13:47.620
I just want to know what you stand on.

00:13:47.620 --> 00:13:49.620
I just want to know what you stand for.

00:13:49.620 --> 00:13:52.620
I stand for truth, justice, and other stuff.

00:13:52.620 --> 00:13:54.620
Okay, well, you want to be a little more specific?

00:13:54.620 --> 00:13:56.620
Like, tell me where you stand on the issues?

00:13:56.620 --> 00:13:57.620
What issues you want to talk about?

00:13:57.620 --> 00:13:59.620
Well, for starters, there's the plan to cut the arts budget.

00:13:59.620 --> 00:14:01.620
There's the appalling nutritional value of the cafeteria meals,

00:14:01.620 --> 00:14:02.620
the whole dress code debate.

00:14:02.620 --> 00:14:05.620
Oh, yeah, and not to mention the whole student privacy issues

00:14:05.620 --> 00:14:06.620
with the locker searches.

00:14:06.620 --> 00:14:08.620
Whoa, slow down. I just decided to run last night.

00:14:08.620 --> 00:14:12.620
Okay, well, I think the man of tomorrow needs to get a platform for today.

00:14:17.620 --> 00:14:20.620
Okay, there's a girls' volleyball game this afternoon.

00:14:20.620 --> 00:14:21.620
I figure you could make an appearance.

00:14:21.620 --> 00:14:22.620
Go with the jock folk.

00:14:22.620 --> 00:14:24.620
Keep Friday night clear. There's a band concert.

00:14:24.620 --> 00:14:27.620
Now, I know they suck, but you got to be seen as a friend of the arts.

00:14:27.620 --> 00:14:28.620
Pete, what about my platform?

00:14:28.620 --> 00:14:31.620
Who cares? If people like you, they'll vote for you.

00:14:31.620 --> 00:14:32.620
But what am I going to say in my speech?

00:14:32.620 --> 00:14:34.620
I don't know. I don't do speeches. I do meet and greets.

00:14:34.620 --> 00:14:36.620
I'll see you at lunch. We can canvass the cafeteria.

00:14:47.620 --> 00:15:15.620
What do they think they are?

00:15:17.620 --> 00:15:33.620
Not now. I have work to do.

00:15:47.620 --> 00:15:53.620
.

00:16:06.620 --> 00:16:09.620
Oi! Any chance you could help with hanging some posters?

00:16:09.620 --> 00:16:12.620
If Pete's convinced he puts my name on enough wall space, I'm guaranteed to win.

00:16:12.620 --> 00:16:14.620
Besides needing to remain an impartial member of the fourth estate,

00:16:14.620 --> 00:16:16.620
I'm still working on my B story.

00:16:16.620 --> 00:16:18.620
CEP find anything new?

00:16:18.620 --> 00:16:21.620
Just that the swarms didn't migrate from any of their usual places.

00:16:21.620 --> 00:16:24.620
But beekeepers from all over the state have found their hives empty.

00:16:24.620 --> 00:16:26.620
It's like the colony's just up and left.

00:16:26.620 --> 00:16:28.620
That's weird. Bees are notorious followers.

00:16:28.620 --> 00:16:31.620
They wouldn't desert their hive without good reason.

00:16:31.620 --> 00:16:34.620
My mom's addicted to Discovery Channel.

00:16:34.620 --> 00:16:36.620
So how goes the platform?

00:16:36.620 --> 00:16:38.620
I haven't started working on it yet.

00:16:38.620 --> 00:16:41.620
I've been so busy meeting new people, I even got invited to parties this weekend.

00:16:41.620 --> 00:16:45.620
I can't believe it only took one day for you to be compromised by the lure of popularity.

00:16:45.620 --> 00:16:48.620
Remind me to pull your funding after I'm elected.

00:16:48.620 --> 00:16:51.620
Speaking of which, where's the latest edition?

00:16:51.620 --> 00:16:54.620
No, no, no, no, no, no, no. I'm not done proofing it yet.

00:16:54.620 --> 00:16:57.620
Clark, I really don't think you should be looking at it just yet. It's not even done.

00:16:57.620 --> 00:16:59.620
Come on, I've been correcting your common issues since your first laptop.

00:16:59.620 --> 00:17:01.620
Clark!

00:17:03.620 --> 00:17:05.619
You endorsed Paul?

00:17:05.619 --> 00:17:07.619
Clark, I had to be objective.

00:17:07.619 --> 00:17:09.619
Paul's still in the race, and he'll be back on his feet again by fall.

00:17:09.619 --> 00:17:12.619
It's great that you're all gung-ho and slogany now,

00:17:12.619 --> 00:17:15.619
but the truth is the only reason you ran is because Pete suckered you into it.

00:17:15.619 --> 00:17:18.619
Paul has a clear stance on issues you have yet to articulate.

00:17:18.619 --> 00:17:20.619
It's nothing personal.

00:17:20.619 --> 00:17:22.619
I understand, Chloe.

00:17:34.619 --> 00:17:37.619
Hey, guys. Taking a break from the campaign show?

00:17:37.619 --> 00:17:40.619
It's amazing how many people in our school I don't know.

00:17:40.619 --> 00:17:43.619
This is just a pit stop. I wanted to take advantage of your two-for-one deal.

00:17:43.619 --> 00:17:46.619
Figure that's the last step before I institute topless waitressing.

00:17:46.619 --> 00:17:49.619
Well, here's to hoping it fails miserably.

00:17:51.619 --> 00:17:53.619
It looks like you have some customers.

00:17:53.619 --> 00:17:55.619
They're only here because Whitney forced them.

00:17:55.619 --> 00:17:57.619
Yeah, I passed by the beanery. They're kind of busy.

00:17:57.619 --> 00:17:59.619
The owner stopped by earlier.

00:17:59.619 --> 00:18:02.619
He said that he was making it his mission to run this place into the ground.

00:18:02.619 --> 00:18:06.619
Then he had the nerve to tell me that it wasn't personal, just business.

00:18:06.619 --> 00:18:09.619
Why does everyone over 40 quote the Godfather?

00:18:09.619 --> 00:18:11.619
I don't know, but it's really annoying.

00:18:13.619 --> 00:18:15.619
So how's political life treating you?

00:18:15.619 --> 00:18:17.619
It's definitely a challenge.

00:18:17.619 --> 00:18:19.619
It shows you who your real friends are.

00:18:19.619 --> 00:18:21.619
How's your speech going?

00:18:21.619 --> 00:18:23.619
I haven't started writing it yet.

00:18:23.619 --> 00:18:25.619
Maybe I could help you with that.

00:18:25.619 --> 00:18:27.619
Come by tomorrow night. We can work on it.

00:18:27.619 --> 00:18:29.619
Really? That'd be great.

00:18:29.619 --> 00:18:31.619
You sure you have enough time?

00:18:31.619 --> 00:18:35.619
Look around. Unless Whitney can coerce the baseball team, I think I can squeeze you in.

00:18:37.619 --> 00:18:39.619
Glad to see business is booming.

00:18:39.619 --> 00:18:41.619
It's hard when even your regular customers blow you off.

00:18:41.619 --> 00:18:43.619
I haven't been busy.

00:18:43.619 --> 00:18:46.619
I'm not blowing you off, Lana. I've had my eye on the situation.

00:18:46.619 --> 00:18:48.619
Waiting for me to fail.

00:18:48.619 --> 00:18:52.619
Most new ventures don't make it. You have to prepare yourself for that possibility.

00:18:52.619 --> 00:18:53.619
I thought you didn't like to lose.

00:18:53.619 --> 00:18:55.619
I don't. But it's not my fight.

00:18:55.619 --> 00:18:58.619
As an investor, you have to know when to cut your losses.

00:18:58.619 --> 00:18:59.619
So what do you suggest I do?

00:18:59.619 --> 00:19:03.619
The Beanery has declared war. If you want to hold on to this place, you need to get creative.

00:19:03.619 --> 00:19:06.619
Be willing to get your hands dirty.

00:19:06.619 --> 00:19:09.619
Don't worry. I'm not suggesting anything illegal.

00:19:09.619 --> 00:19:11.619
To quote the Godfather, it's time to go to the mattresses.

00:19:11.619 --> 00:19:15.619
That movie should be banned from basic cable.

00:19:21.619 --> 00:19:23.619
Don't ask.

00:19:30.619 --> 00:19:32.619
Felice, can I talk to you a minute?

00:19:32.619 --> 00:19:35.619
You've got 55 seconds left. Go.

00:19:35.619 --> 00:19:37.619
I've made a decision.

00:19:37.619 --> 00:19:39.619
You're planning on dropping out.

00:19:39.619 --> 00:19:41.619
No, I've decided you need to drop out.

00:19:44.619 --> 00:19:46.619
Trust me. That's not going to happen.

00:19:46.619 --> 00:19:49.619
In case you haven't heard, I'm the frontrunner.

00:19:49.619 --> 00:19:53.619
That's because these drones wouldn't know a qualified candidate if they saw one.

00:19:53.619 --> 00:19:55.619
That's the problem with this place.

00:19:55.619 --> 00:19:58.619
It's like a hive with two queens.

00:19:58.619 --> 00:20:02.619
Well, if you knew anything about nature, you'd realize one always goes down.

00:20:02.619 --> 00:20:05.619
You know what? You're a freak.

00:20:07.619 --> 00:20:08.619
Okay, have it your way.

00:20:09.619 --> 00:20:11.619
But just remember, I did ask nicely.

00:20:17.619 --> 00:20:19.619
Gabby, you were the best part of my day.

00:20:19.619 --> 00:20:21.619
Thank you, Mr. Luther.

00:20:24.619 --> 00:20:25.619
You're not Gabby.

00:20:25.619 --> 00:20:27.619
She couldn't make it.

00:20:27.619 --> 00:20:29.619
I think now would be a good time for you to leave, Miss Castle.

00:20:29.619 --> 00:20:31.619
Do people always do what you say?

00:20:31.619 --> 00:20:33.619
Is that unusual?

00:20:33.619 --> 00:20:36.619
I thought you said you appreciated persistence.

00:20:36.619 --> 00:20:38.619
Besides, aren't I doing a good job?

00:20:39.619 --> 00:20:41.619
I'm lucky for you.

00:20:41.619 --> 00:20:44.619
It took a while to figure out what would tempt you.

00:20:44.619 --> 00:20:46.619
And then it hit me.

00:20:48.619 --> 00:20:51.619
It's not your picture on the cover of the journal so much as the words,

00:20:51.619 --> 00:20:54.619
Son outshines father in the caption.

00:20:54.619 --> 00:20:56.619
How am I doing?

00:20:56.619 --> 00:20:58.619
A little lower.

00:20:58.619 --> 00:21:00.619
Let me guess.

00:21:00.619 --> 00:21:03.619
Your editor promised you your own column if you land me.

00:21:03.619 --> 00:21:05.619
So you can imagine how appreciative I'd be.

00:21:05.619 --> 00:21:06.619
I'm not.

00:21:06.619 --> 00:21:07.619
I'm not.

00:21:07.619 --> 00:21:09.619
I don't think I can.

00:21:09.619 --> 00:21:10.619
Tell me, Lex.

00:21:10.619 --> 00:21:13.619
Would you say my chances are above average or below?

00:21:13.619 --> 00:21:16.619
Like I said, I always appreciate persistence.

00:21:16.619 --> 00:21:18.619
You won't regret this?

00:21:18.619 --> 00:21:20.619
Not yet, Miss Castle.

00:21:21.619 --> 00:21:23.619
I paid for an hour.

00:21:30.619 --> 00:21:31.619
I'm sorry.

00:21:31.619 --> 00:21:32.619
I'm sorry.

00:21:32.619 --> 00:21:33.619
I'm sorry.

00:21:33.619 --> 00:21:34.619
I'm sorry.

00:21:34.619 --> 00:21:35.619
I'm sorry.

00:21:35.619 --> 00:21:36.619
I'm sorry.

00:21:36.619 --> 00:21:37.619
I'm sorry.

00:22:02.619 --> 00:22:03.619
Police, Chandler.

00:22:03.619 --> 00:22:04.619
What's the problem?

00:22:05.619 --> 00:22:07.619
Take him off, take him off, take him off.

00:22:07.619 --> 00:22:08.519
Take him off.

00:22:19.519 --> 00:22:21.019
Gotta get in.

00:22:21.019 --> 00:22:22.519
Go for Clark.

00:22:22.519 --> 00:22:23.419
Go for Clark.

00:22:27.019 --> 00:22:28.399
I thought getting out there and meeting people

00:22:28.399 --> 00:22:29.599
would be the worst part.

00:22:29.599 --> 00:22:31.039
It's actually kind of fun.

00:22:31.039 --> 00:22:32.939
I'm glad you feel that way, because according

00:22:32.940 --> 00:22:38.220
to my latest lunchtime poll, you've got a shot.

00:22:38.220 --> 00:22:40.220
Hey.

00:22:40.220 --> 00:22:41.120
Hey.

00:22:45.700 --> 00:22:46.600
How's it going?

00:22:46.600 --> 00:22:47.500
Just answer no comment.

00:22:47.500 --> 00:22:48.600
That way she can't misquote you.

00:22:52.120 --> 00:22:53.380
Did you hear about Felice?

00:22:53.380 --> 00:22:55.160
Yeah, I was just at the medical center.

00:22:55.160 --> 00:22:56.559
She was stung way worse than Paul.

00:22:56.559 --> 00:22:59.940
She's in a coma.

00:22:59.940 --> 00:23:02.519
Two candidates attacked in a week.

00:23:02.519 --> 00:23:04.319
It's a pretty freaky coincidence.

00:23:04.319 --> 00:23:06.420
I think we've moved past coincidence.

00:23:06.420 --> 00:23:07.759
What do you think's going on?

00:23:07.759 --> 00:23:09.960
I don't know, but remember last year, Sasha's accident,

00:23:09.960 --> 00:23:12.180
when she was stung by a whole hive of bees?

00:23:12.180 --> 00:23:14.319
You think because of that, she's somehow controlling them?

00:23:19.119 --> 00:23:20.180
It's a theory.

00:23:20.180 --> 00:23:23.859
Yeah, by several leaps and bounds, but I'll look into it.

00:23:23.859 --> 00:23:25.599
In the meantime, watch your back.

00:23:32.519 --> 00:23:35.420
I just heard about Felice.

00:23:35.420 --> 00:23:37.019
Weird, huh?

00:23:37.019 --> 00:23:39.319
Sometimes things just happen for a reason.

00:23:39.319 --> 00:23:41.819
She didn't care about this election as much as me.

00:23:41.819 --> 00:23:45.720
She wasn't my favorite person, but no one deserves that.

00:23:45.720 --> 00:23:48.019
Well, the good news is, you don't have to run anymore.

00:23:48.019 --> 00:23:49.519
Well, with Felice out of the picture,

00:23:49.519 --> 00:23:51.720
the best thing you can do is let me run things.

00:23:51.720 --> 00:23:53.220
What about democracy?

00:23:53.220 --> 00:23:55.220
Don't you believe people should have freedom of choice?

00:23:55.220 --> 00:23:58.019
Look, Clark, I really need this.

00:23:58.019 --> 00:23:59.519
My parents are really worried about me.

00:23:59.519 --> 00:24:00.619
I'm not going to let them get away with it.

00:24:00.619 --> 00:24:01.619
I'm going to get out of here.

00:24:01.619 --> 00:24:02.319
I'm going to get out of here.

00:24:02.319 --> 00:24:03.119
My parents are writing me to win.

00:24:03.119 --> 00:24:05.819
They think if I don't win, I won't get into a good college.

00:24:05.819 --> 00:24:06.819
You have other activities.

00:24:06.819 --> 00:24:08.319
This is my thing.

00:24:08.319 --> 00:24:09.919
Why don't you just drop out?

00:24:09.919 --> 00:24:11.220
I'm sorry.

00:24:11.220 --> 00:24:14.319
I have my own reasons to see this through.

00:24:14.319 --> 00:24:17.220
You're making a mistake.

00:24:17.220 --> 00:24:18.220
That sounded like a threat.

00:24:21.519 --> 00:24:23.019
You wouldn't happen to know how those bees went up

00:24:23.019 --> 00:24:25.319
attacking Paul and Felice, would you?

00:24:25.319 --> 00:24:27.319
Are you accusing me of something, Clark?

00:24:27.319 --> 00:24:29.359
I just find it interesting that a swarm of bees

00:24:29.359 --> 00:24:30.980
would attack two candidates in this election.

00:24:32.319 --> 00:24:35.519
Well, I don't think that's a threat.

00:24:35.519 --> 00:24:37.119
My thoughts are somebody's behind it.

00:24:50.119 --> 00:24:52.119
Good start.

00:24:52.119 --> 00:24:54.519
My trash bin has three drafts, and nothing I can come up with

00:24:54.519 --> 00:24:56.319
sounds presidential enough.

00:24:56.319 --> 00:24:57.319
Don't have to sound presidential.

00:24:57.319 --> 00:24:58.619
You just have to say what you believe.

00:24:58.619 --> 00:25:00.319
Once you answer that, the rest is easy.

00:25:00.319 --> 00:25:02.419
Not a lot of work to do then.

00:25:02.419 --> 00:25:05.700
Not as much as I have here.

00:25:05.700 --> 00:25:07.319
Lana, I know you're having a tough time,

00:25:07.319 --> 00:25:09.559
but I really think it's amazing what you've done with the place.

00:25:09.559 --> 00:25:11.980
This was just going to be the start.

00:25:11.980 --> 00:25:14.559
My dream was to restore the old theater completely.

00:25:14.559 --> 00:25:17.339
The projector, the screen, show old movies.

00:25:17.339 --> 00:25:18.359
Just not the Godfather.

00:25:20.779 --> 00:25:22.319
Come on, Clark, back to the speech.

00:25:22.319 --> 00:25:25.480
You have to decide what you believe in.

00:25:25.480 --> 00:25:29.000
I believe in my friends and their dreams.

00:25:29.000 --> 00:25:31.640
What if their dreams come crashing down around them?

00:25:31.640 --> 00:25:33.140
Nothing's crashing down around you, Lana.

00:25:33.140 --> 00:25:35.440
Not while I'm here.

00:25:35.440 --> 00:25:36.339
Thanks, Clark.

00:25:40.680 --> 00:25:41.500
Did you hear that?

00:25:44.279 --> 00:25:45.579
Yeah, it was coming from over there.

00:25:48.339 --> 00:25:51.160
And there.

00:25:51.160 --> 00:25:52.059
What is it?

00:25:59.000 --> 00:26:01.200
Lean in!

00:26:01.200 --> 00:26:01.900
Oh!

00:26:01.900 --> 00:26:02.579
Hey!

00:26:09.779 --> 00:26:10.819
Hurry, man.

00:26:10.819 --> 00:26:12.039
Oh.

00:26:12.039 --> 00:26:15.619
Oh, hey.

00:26:18.420 --> 00:26:19.480
Oh no!

00:26:21.220 --> 00:26:22.119
Oh.

00:26:22.119 --> 00:26:22.720
Oh.

00:26:22.720 --> 00:26:23.420
Oh.

00:26:23.420 --> 00:26:23.819
Oh.

00:26:23.819 --> 00:26:24.319
Oh.

00:26:24.319 --> 00:26:24.819
Oh.

00:26:24.819 --> 00:26:26.299
Oh.

00:26:26.299 --> 00:26:27.619
Oh.

00:26:27.619 --> 00:26:28.279
Oh.

00:26:28.279 --> 00:26:28.779
Oh.

00:26:28.779 --> 00:26:28.880
Oh.

00:26:28.880 --> 00:26:28.960
Oh.

00:26:28.960 --> 00:26:28.980
Oh.

00:26:28.980 --> 00:26:58.960
I'm sorry.

00:26:58.980 --> 00:27:28.960
I'm sorry.

00:27:28.980 --> 00:27:29.960
I need to find Sasha.

00:27:30.220 --> 00:27:31.460
Do you think she has something to do with it?

00:27:31.700 --> 00:27:33.620
Yes. I just don't know how she's controlling the bees.

00:27:34.720 --> 00:27:35.799
You need to call Chloe.

00:27:36.160 --> 00:27:37.180
We're still not really talking.

00:27:37.660 --> 00:27:39.000
Can you believe she didn't endorse me?

00:27:39.860 --> 00:27:41.220
Well, if I were in her position,

00:27:41.339 --> 00:27:42.720
I probably would have done the same thing.

00:27:43.339 --> 00:27:44.460
She's just trying to be objective,

00:27:44.680 --> 00:27:46.059
and she endorsed the person who she thought

00:27:46.059 --> 00:27:47.480
was most qualified for the job.

00:27:47.579 --> 00:27:48.460
Yeah, but still...

00:27:48.460 --> 00:27:50.880
Clark, you said you believed in your friends.

00:27:51.799 --> 00:27:53.220
She only did what she thought was right.

00:27:58.980 --> 00:28:22.980
I don't know.

00:28:22.980 --> 00:28:23.200
Chloe.

00:28:23.480 --> 00:28:24.519
Lana told me about the talent.

00:28:24.700 --> 00:28:25.380
Thanks for the call.

00:28:26.420 --> 00:28:26.779
Sorry.

00:28:27.460 --> 00:28:28.599
It's all right. I'm not mad.

00:28:29.779 --> 00:28:30.980
Chloe, uh...

00:28:32.120 --> 00:28:34.200
I don't hold it against you,

00:28:34.259 --> 00:28:35.440
the endorsement, I mean.

00:28:36.720 --> 00:28:38.180
Thanks. I could have warned you, though.

00:28:39.900 --> 00:28:41.339
I just don't like being in a fight with you.

00:28:42.440 --> 00:28:44.000
Yeah, it wasn't my favorite part, either.

00:28:47.339 --> 00:28:49.700
Everything has changed in my life in the last year.

00:28:50.099 --> 00:28:51.980
My parents, Lana...

00:28:54.720 --> 00:28:56.259
The only thing constant has been you.

00:28:57.099 --> 00:28:58.019
I'm glad for that, Chloe.

00:28:58.980 --> 00:28:59.680
I like you.

00:28:59.860 --> 00:29:01.019
You're the fastest girl I've ever met.

00:29:01.059 --> 00:29:02.039
I like you, too.

00:29:02.140 --> 00:29:02.819
Hm-mm.

00:29:02.880 --> 00:29:03.960
No, that was aboutter being with you.

00:29:07.980 --> 00:29:09.319
You know every flower blooms on the inside.

00:29:09.519 --> 00:29:11.960
To me, that determination one of a kind is something

00:29:12.039 --> 00:29:14.079
the heart of any petitioner feels like the harvesting of.

00:29:14.079 --> 00:29:15.160
That's what you're like as a girl.

00:29:15.180 --> 00:29:17.700
Your presence slowly doesn't really

00:29:17.799 --> 00:29:19.160
make anyone feel like it.

00:29:19.279 --> 00:29:20.819
You haven't thought about me at all.

00:29:21.059 --> 00:29:22.539
That conversation you had with your family...

00:29:22.539 --> 00:29:22.980
Yeah.

00:29:23.079 --> 00:29:24.640
You let them know.

00:29:24.740 --> 00:29:26.519
They had no chance of getting away with it.

00:29:26.559 --> 00:29:27.720
It's the feeling.

00:29:27.720 --> 00:29:29.059
She picked that up when she fell in the hive?

00:29:30.180 --> 00:29:32.100
She was stung over a thousand times.

00:29:32.700 --> 00:29:33.779
They were Africanized honeybees,

00:29:33.839 --> 00:29:35.940
and the doctors didn't hold out much hope because she was allergic.

00:29:36.960 --> 00:29:39.200
How do they account for the miracle recovery?

00:29:39.539 --> 00:29:40.140
They don't.

00:29:40.700 --> 00:29:43.900
And neither could I until I found out the accident happened in Schuster's Gorge.

00:29:44.440 --> 00:29:45.740
That's the deepest crater in town.

00:29:45.980 --> 00:29:47.519
Yeah, you do the meteorite math.

00:29:47.839 --> 00:29:49.660
The bees did something to her to make her their queen bee.

00:29:50.180 --> 00:29:52.160
Now all the bees in the state are taking their cue from her.

00:29:52.519 --> 00:29:54.839
And they're helping her make Smallville High her own personal hive.

00:29:54.980 --> 00:29:55.720
We'd better find her.

00:29:55.720 --> 00:29:58.259
If she doesn't like the way the vote goes, the school won't be a pretty sight.

00:29:58.620 --> 00:29:59.279
Neither will she.

00:29:59.680 --> 00:30:00.920
Bees are only loyal to a point.

00:30:01.220 --> 00:30:03.460
Once she loses control, her scent will change and the bees will know.

00:30:04.120 --> 00:30:04.839
They won't be happy.

00:30:13.259 --> 00:30:14.759
Thought you wanted to meet somewhere private.

00:30:16.539 --> 00:30:18.200
Lately, this has been passing for that.

00:30:21.440 --> 00:30:24.000
Thanks for agreeing to see me. I just want to get a few more quotes.

00:30:24.000 --> 00:30:24.480
Hmm.

00:30:25.120 --> 00:30:25.700
How's the article?

00:30:25.720 --> 00:30:26.559
How's the article going?

00:30:27.759 --> 00:30:29.559
I think people are gonna see you in a whole new light.

00:30:29.799 --> 00:30:30.960
